TITLE: Creating Request Metadata for Cross-Chain Calls in Solidity
DESCRIPTION: Function that encodes parameters into the requestMetadata bytes object required by iSend. It packages gas limits, prices, relayer fees, and other cross-chain communication settings.
SOURCE: https://github.com/oasisprotocol/docs/blob/main/docs/build/opl/router-protocol/interface.md#2025-04-16_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: solidity
CODE:
```
function getRequestMetadata(
    uint64 destGasLimit,
    uint64 destGasPrice,
    uint64 ackGasLimit,
    uint64 ackGasPrice,
    uint128 relayerFees,
    uint8 ackType,
    bool isReadCall,
    string memory asmAddress
) public pure returns (bytes memory) {
    bytes memory requestMetadata = abi.encodePacked(
    destGasLimit,
    destGasPrice,
    ackGasLimit,
    ackGasPrice,
    relayerFees,
    ackType,
    isReadCall,
    asmAddress
    );
    return requestMetadata;
}
```

